{%- comment -%}
  vf-process.liquid

  Four-stage numbered strip on Obsidian. Step numbers in Gold Mono,
  hairline column dividers between steps, single text-link CTA right.

  Schema contract: docs/section-schemas.md §3
  Visual reference: ui_kits/website/Process.jsx

  Judgement calls
  ───────────────
  1. Step numbers use block.settings.number per schema doc §3.
     vf-mono rendered with size: 'base' (11px = --vf-fs-mono-1).
     Schema doc §3 hardcoded entry says "Mono, 9px" (micro) which falls
     below the CLAUDE.md §3 accessibility floor of 11px. Base wins.

  2. schema doc §3 lists a 'body' richtext section setting. The JSX has
     no body copy placement in Process. Setting is included in schema for
     contract compliance but not rendered. Add a placement here if the
     design is ever revised to include it.

  3. 'method_label' and 'method_url' are present in the JSX (Button
     variant="text") but absent from schema doc §3. Added as settings;
     schema doc §3 should be updated to include them.

  4. Column dividers are border-left on steps 2–4 (none on :first-child).
     These are structural grid separators, not left-border accent cards.
     CLAUDE.md §4 ban on left-border accent cards does not apply here.
     On mobile they rotate to border-top separators between stacked rows.

  5. vf-process__link styles scoped to this section's {% style %} block.
     vf-tokens.css already sets :focus-visible for [class^="vf-"] so the
     focus ring is inherited without duplication. Extract to a global
     .vf-link rule in vf-tokens.css if a second section needs this pattern.

  6. Tablet 3-col stage omitted per session instruction (match the JSX
     kit, one breakpoint only). Schema doc §3 hardcoded entry says
     "3-col tablet" — schema doc needs updating to match.

  7. Headline uses --vf-fs-h-section (added to vf-tokens.css in same
     release). JSX value was clamp(2.2rem, 3.4vw, 3.4rem).

  8. Step title letter-spacing: JSX uses -0.005em; no exact token exists.
     --vf-track-tight (-0.01em) is the closest and is used here.
{%- endcomment -%}

<section
  class="vf-process"
  aria-labelledby="vf-process-title"
  data-section-id="{{ section.id }}"
>
  <div class="vf-process__inner">

    <div class="vf-process__header">
      <div class="vf-process__header-left">
        {%- if section.settings.eyebrow != blank -%}
          {%- render 'vf-eyebrow', text: section.settings.eyebrow -%}
        {%- endif -%}
        <h2 id="vf-process-title" class="vf-process__headline">
          {{- section.settings.headline_part_1 | escape -}}<br>
          <em>{{- section.settings.headline_part_2 | escape -}}</em>
        </h2>
      </div>
      {%- if section.settings.method_label != blank -%}
        <a
          class="vf-process__link"
          href="{{ section.settings.method_url }}"
        >
          {{- section.settings.method_label | escape -}}
        </a>
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>

    <div class="vf-process__grid" role="list">
      {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
        <div class="vf-process__step" role="listitem" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
          {%- render 'vf-mono', text: block.settings.number, color: 'gold', size: 'base' -%}
          <h3 class="vf-process__step-title">
            {{- block.settings.title | escape -}}
          </h3>
          <div class="vf-process__step-body">
            {{- block.settings.body -}}
          </div>
        </div>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

{% style %}
  .vf-process {
    background: var(--vf-obsidian);
    padding: var(--vf-s-9) var(--vf-grid-margin-d);
    border-bottom: var(--vf-hairline) solid var(--vf-border-2);
  }

  .vf-process__inner {
    max-width: var(--vf-grid-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .vf-process__header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-end;
    margin-bottom: var(--vf-s-7);
  }

  .vf-process__header-left {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--vf-s-4);
    max-width: 580px;
  }

  .vf-process__headline {
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-display);
    font-weight: var(--vf-w-light);
    font-size: var(--vf-fs-h-section);
    line-height: var(--vf-lh-h);
    letter-spacing: var(--vf-track-tight);
    color: var(--vf-fg-1);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .vf-process__headline em {
    color: var(--vf-fg-3);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .vf-process__link {
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-body);
    font-size: var(--vf-fs-body);
    font-weight: var(--vf-w-light);
    color: var(--vf-fg-2);
    text-decoration: none;
    letter-spacing: var(--vf-track-label);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    min-height: var(--vf-hit-min);
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: color var(--vf-dur-fast) var(--vf-ease);
  }

  .vf-process__link:hover {
    color: var(--vf-fg-1);
  }

  .vf-process__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
  }

  .vf-process__step {
    padding: 0 var(--vf-s-5);
    border-left: var(--vf-hairline) solid var(--vf-border-2);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--vf-s-3);
  }

  .vf-process__step:first-child {
    border-left: none;
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  .vf-process__step-title {
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-display);
    font-weight: var(--vf-w-regular);
    font-size: var(--vf-fs-h3);
    line-height: var(--vf-lh-h);
    letter-spacing: var(--vf-track-tight);
    color: var(--vf-fg-1);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .vf-process__step-body {
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-body);
    font-weight: var(--vf-w-light);
    font-size: var(--vf-fs-body);
    line-height: var(--vf-lh-body);
    color: var(--vf-fg-3);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .vf-process__step-body p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 749px) {
    .vf-process {
      padding: var(--vf-s-8) var(--vf-grid-margin-m);
    }

    .vf-process__header {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: var(--vf-s-5);
      margin-bottom: var(--vf-s-6);
    }

    .vf-process__headline {
      max-width: none;
    }

    .vf-process__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .vf-process__step {
      border-left: none;
      padding: var(--vf-s-4) 0;
      border-top: var(--vf-hairline) solid var(--vf-border-2);
    }

    .vf-process__step:first-child {
      border-top: none;
      padding-top: 0;
    }
  }
{% endstyle %}

{% schema %}
